name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Place one can hear frogs bark like dogs. They are really loud. Experience the natural smell of farms.Love to be there often by cycling. But, at the point of time Road to this place is rather dangerous for cycling especially weekdays. Big trucks are rushing and over taking very close to cyclists.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Slightly disappointed. Was expecting more, like a mini Sungei Buloh.
Shuttle bus service to the park is provided on weekends. Park area opened to public is restricted to 1km long service road, leading to an observation tower. From the tower, you get to see the greenery around the banks of Kranji river. Good place for bird watching and photography.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: It was quiet and only a few people this morning. The route from the gate to the raptor can be further improve by planting more plants in both side of the road. Right now it is more like just normal plants growing on both side. You will need a pair of good binoculars otherwise hardly see any birds on the ground level.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
We walked to the most ulu park in Singapore’s countryside

Kranji Marshes is located at Neo Tiew area near Kranji

We didnt know there was shuttle bus and had to walk across from Lim Chu Kang area

But was nice to see all the farms

Really enjoyed the biodiversity here

Remember to check for shuttle bus!

Tiktok: unconventionalpassionss

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: If you don't drive, use the free shuttle service from Kranji MRT; take bus 925 and walk from Sungei Buloh wetland reserve to Neo Tiew Road or take bus 975 and walk from Lim Chu Kang Road to Neo Tiew Road.  Went in late afternoon and not a lot of people - like the tranquillity

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Always my favourite place for nature and macro photography. Come the wet season, frogs in heat will be perfect for nature photographers at the pond (entrance).  Best on weekdays when the crowd are thin and parking easily available.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
The place was easy to find. It was just beside Gallop Kranji Farm Resort.
Once you've parked, you can see Baya Weaver birds' nests in the reeds and if you stand for a while, you'll see the weaver birds flying to their nests. Further in, you can see a Pied Fantail in its cup-sized nest in the tree near the rest area.
There is so much to see here and there are hides and the raptor tower further in which gives you a good view of the surrounding area.
I would come back here again to see if I can spot more birds.

It is kid friendly too as my child was able to walk all the way in and up the tower and back. The whole trip took about an hour for us. Parking is very limited. There seems to be a shuttle bus service on weekends and public holidays which could help people get there, which is a great service for a public park.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Path less taken with almost nobody around. Very secluded place. Some degree of neglect as well. But definitely a good stroll if weather is good. Takes less than 2 hours for the loop.
Access is not easy.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Walking from Neo Tiew Rd to kranji Marshes around 2.5km ,this place not to big but is fun and relax the mind by hear many sound of birds , walking surrounded watching the birds,quite interesting. 🚶🔭👍

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: A small park suitable for a short walk or bird watching. The actual Marsh area is disappointingly small, and if just walking can be covered in less than 10 minutes. There is a long, paved road between the Carpark and the Marsh area. Unless you're lucky enough to spot a raptor, the car park will likely offer the closest up view of birds in the area, e.g. Golden-backed weavers.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
(end October 2021) ... Perhaps am I unlucky for birds watching but with the noise around with all the construction works, don't expect to see a lot. Moreover 2/3 are closed, except the tower and 2 places just nearby nothing  (so the map is not what you can do.... Unfortunately) ....
The good point, go to Bollywood Vegi nearby and spend good time.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: From entrance to attraction it’s a pretty boring 10-15min walk. Path is mostly not shaded so can be uncomfortable in a hot day. The raptor lookout tower is nice but the surrounding around can be explored within 15 min. Not particularly interesting but if you want to avoid crowd and do a <1H walk it can be done here.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Didn't expect half the park to be closed! Very disappointed. Overall a less crowded park compared to the others, since it's quite remote.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Nice place to watch the sunset or sunrise from the Raptor Tower. Great place to bring kids. The walk from main entrance to the Tower is about 15min. Not very crowded. Do carry sunscreen and insect repellant. Drinking water and toilets at the entrance. Do carry a water bottle. Pls don't litter.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Interesting 10 to15mins walk to the view tower and observation hut. Just a small area, can be explored in 15mins. Bring binoculars...

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Great outdoors venue, for walks, and especially great for birdwatching. Lots of butterflies in the morning. Dragonflies too!  Not crowded as it is not so accessible as public transport is limited there.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Fantastic nature spot with scenic views out over the Marshes and nearby conservation areas, teeming with birds, butterflies and other wildlife.

Well worth a visit to explore the tower, grass bridge and to also spend some time watching the world go by in the hives.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Free:
Water
Parking
Toilet

Quite a nice view from the tower. And if one is more free spirited like me, stay under the shelter of the tower, its quite comfortable to enjoy the breeze and the area is clean enough for a forested area. Just help maintain the cleanliness.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
If you want to go to a nature park with basically no people but a great place to be, here is definitely the one you would want to go to, just be careful trying to go there without a car, especially on weekdays

Also good place for bird watching

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Our first time to Kranji Marshes on a Monday afternoon to avoid crowds.  It was very quiet and peaceful trail at 4pm under the hot sun ☀️

Note: only bus to go there during weekdays is bus 925.

Going there during weekdays are quite inconvenient and inaccessible as walking will take you hours to arrive, so we took a taxi in.

The trail is very peaceful and quiet and it’s worth going if you are an avid bird lovers.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Easy walk (1km to the tower) with great greenery and wildlife to be seen. Glad to have caught so many birds, but think it would have been better if I went earlier because then it would be less hot (I went at 10am). There are some unshaded parts on the way in so wear lots of sunblock! The view from the raptor tower is great and the breeze is nice.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
5 star photography location. Highly Recommend for a relaxed time to relax and enjoy the sight!

But even if you are not there for photos you will notice many families enjoying the view. Took amazing sunset pictures and left slightly before 7pm. You will get to see part of malaysia from a tower along the trail. No mosquitoes during my visit which is quite surprising.

Come with a camera, binoculars, insect repellant.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Nice walk, lots of birds. Great place for bird enthusiasts. I expected a lot more from the park, can't really get to the marshes, no boardwalk. It was over really fast.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: This looked so promising but it turned out to be very disappointing. After walking down a service road, we found the bridge to the boardwalk was locked, with Three locks. That section, which is most of the park, is only for guided tours. I understand the need for conservancy, but hey guys, why not put a notice at the park entrance?

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Perfect place to catch sunsets. Stroll for a short time. Also good for birdwatching. Climb upto the raptor tower to have a 360 view of the marshland.
It is generally just a short hike from the gate to the tower and the look out, so its to spend with the whole family.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Quite out of place and a long drive in but the  trip is quite worth it. The walk to the tower isn't too difficult but can be a little hot under Singapore's hot sun. Do bring water if you intend to visit. Also, u can take great pictures of birds here so for those who like to take wildlife pics, do bring along your gear!

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: I would say this is a preview of Sungei Buloh Nature Reserve. It's one km walk from the main entrance to the viewing tower. You need to be a serious bird watcher in order to spend meaningful time here.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Very far from mrt station and very difficult to find but the place was okay. Good for bird watching. Be sure to bring insect repelant when you go there.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: One of the rare and quiet places in Singapore with a lovely view.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
For nature lovers obviously. Very few visitors so if you prefer trees and insects more than people this is great for you. Parking is limited but I wouldn't worry about getting a vacant lot to park. From the main entrance to the end of the trail it's quite some distance away so choose the timing appropriately, you want to avoid walking under hot sun as there's no shade.

There's a observatory tower (main attraction) with some nice scenic views especially during sunset and 2 hides for bird watchers to hunker down and arm themselves with binoculars. Overall it's an interesting family outing but few attractions and a lot of walking without shades.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
A bit further than Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve. We weren’t sure at first, but when we arrived, we saw a number of cars parked. Be careful of speed hump, they are high.

It’s about a 1-km easy walk to the Raptor Tower. The path is paved and very straight. There are quite a number of boar droppings.

When we got to the Raptor Tower area, we could see a number of bird watching areas. There are some wooden seating to observe the birds. I’m surprised to see a few bird watchers.

Not as crowded as the other parks.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: It's a nature reserved park. Nice to have a walk with family and kids. Just a glimpse of it cos we are tired from cycling. Only visited til the raptor tower.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Small pond near the carpark area. Walk about 10 minutes down a paved road and you'll see a viewing tower. That's as far as you can go although the park's map displays a larger area that you are allowed to trek.

Relatively disappointing due to the small trekking area. Would be good if the park's on-site map can be updated.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Good to explore
Bird watching spot
Lot of millipede & centipede & lizards 🦎
Nice place to take pic

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Suitable for bird watchers. NPark Core area guided tour (once a month Saturday evening- have to prior register via website) is highly recommended, then you can spot the common and endangered birds..... core conservation area is rocky and actually only suitable for adults (not for children). Bring binoculars and insect repellents!

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Full of greenery but beware of mosquitos

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Nice place! But area to walk is quite small
Best to have a car to get here, if not there's kranji shuttle bus! From Kranji mrt and back every 2 hours

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Wonderful & peaceful nature place with many birds, butterflies, reptiles, dragonflies. Seasonal from November to March. Nothing much to do. Therefore when you go there, don't forget your binoculars / telephoto lens.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: It is a beautiful tranquil small park. Great for people who own a BIG AXX camera lenses for bird-watching. If you just go there for sight seeing, you will be disappointed. But it will be a good place to clear your own need-to-visit list, one time visit place.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
If you have tried Sungei Below then this is the alternative to visit.
A freshwater marshland, derived from the damming of the Kranji River to form the Kranji Reservoir, became seen as an important habitat. Nature Society Singapore (NSS) drafted a proposal highlighting its conservation value in 1990. This was accepted and included in the government Singapore Green Plan 1993. The 54-hectare site includes woodland and wetlands. NSS adopted the stretch of wetlands in 2008 and supported by sponsorship carried out a restoration program in cooperation with PUB and NParks. It was in 2005 that the area was recategorised as a park and named "Kranji Marshes Park". The parkland was opened to the public on 1 February 2016.The area is home to a number of endangered birds, and at least 170 species have been recorded.

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes

review_text:

I suggest u bring a stool and chill there (if u are the only one there). Cos that's about all u would love about this place - the view. I felt like I was overseas, surrounded by nature.
The size of the place was small, not a lot to explore. It's a good place to bring ur kids of they don't mind walking 1km to get there and another 1km to get back to the entrance.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: A very beautiful park and quite well shaded, only transportation problem when visit on a weekday (25.12.2022)

name: Kranji Marshes

review_text:

review_text: This place is small and tranquil. Good for evening runs so that we can view the sunset at the raptor tower.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Quiet with plenty of birds. There's a roughly 1km forested walk along a road from the entrance to the actual park area. There's a raptor hide overlooking a wide swathe of the wetlands which is great for bird watching. There's also a stream and a small pond .

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: There is a free transport from kranji mrt at certain timing. Place is not too big.

name: Kranji Marshes

review_text: A natural and serene for small group or individual to find solace in a hustle bustle of city life.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: A short 20 mins trail (one way). Very quiet and peaceful but nothing much to see here and quite uneventful. There are several bird watching huts but we didn't manage to see the unique bird species during out visit.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
A hidden gem i found through maps.

An extension of Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve and mainly a place for bird watchers.

Shuttle buses are avail to and fro from SBWR. Limited parking lots are avail so consider going off peak hours.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Wonderful quiet place for walking and a family outing. Especially good for bird watching. West Marsh was open yesterday for a few hours to allow viewing of migratory birds. The volunteers on duty were so knowledgable and helpful. I really enjoyed my visit. A limited bus service runs to the MRT (and other local places of interest) so it is possible to visit without a car. The website contains up to date information on events etc.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: This place is haunted .. plse leave ard 4 pm .. eerie at nite

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Not much to see.  There is a 1-2km trail surrounded by loud construction on one side.  There is a viewing tower which gets you an uninteresting view.  Everything else is closed off and it would have been nice if there was a sign at the entrance on the maps indicating this, or even better if this was indicated on the website.

This should actually be renamed "Telephoto Lens Park".  All it is is basically hordes of people with telephoto lenses (bigger than the kind you see at the Super Bowl photographing who knows what.  We saw one of the birds listed on the guiding plaques, and I bet I could have seen it in Tanglin as well.  The vending machines don't take NETS or credit cards so bring your own water, or bring cash because there is NOTHING in that area.

Don't bother coming from the city, it's not worth the $25 Grab ride (Each way).

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Nothing much here so I don't really recommend this place but you may still wanna check this place out if you wanna have a getaway from city life

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: The area open to the public is rather small

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Really green and quiet place to spend some time.

Definitely a good place to go if you're a birdwatcher, even just walking along the path we came across a gorgeous yellow feathered friend.

Other than that, a big part of the route (core conservation areas) is limited to pre-arranged guided walks. Might have to consider going for that though, as there's a really nice floating boardwalk we managed to peek at.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Tower is about 15 mins walk from main entrance. Not much to see until you reach the tower, more for those who enjoy birds watching .

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: "Good morning... I just wanna say that."

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Dangerous walk to destination from end of bus stop as there is no proper pedestrian walk path had to walk near edge of road where many heavy trucks plying. Shuttle service only on weekend

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: We had planned to spend an afternoon exploring the marshes but only a very small section is accessible, the majority is behind a locked gate and only available if you go on a guided tour. Better off visiting the nearby wetlands as more of it is open to the public.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: I loved the break from the city sounds. Nature dominated with its own sounds and smells. The birds, trees, wind, sun made the experience so different and exciting. We had a casual walk and enjoyed every intake of breath.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Good place for bird photography.
There are no MRT Stations or Bus stop near by, so bettet use your own cars, taxi or grab.
Here is a bit small area than I expected but I found Stork-billed Kingfisher, White-throated Kingfisher and many raptors here.
Would recoomend for those who loves birding.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Unless you're a bird watcher, you can only enjoy the hike. To 'catch' the birds, you must make sure the season of migration is known or else you will be disappointed.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Was at bollywood veggies for lunch and needed to burn of the nasi lemak so we toured the farm and walked over to the marshes to soak up the sun. Cool view from the raptor tower! Just note its a short turnaround walk and not connected to the wetlands. You will have to walk via the roads for that.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: a place for bird watcher and smell of nature.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Beautiful quiet place and a haven for bird lovers. The nparks or nature society tours are ideal but I enjoyed the birdwatching with my 6 year old even without venturing to the core conservation area. Sunbirds, blue throated Bee eater, baya weaver, black capped Kingfisher, storks/egrets/herons, various raptors, red-wattled lapwing, purple swamphen spotted here along with common birds like the glossy starling, oriole, yellow vented Bulbul, green pigeon etc. I believe there are so much more yet to be discovered! There's a kranji express shuttle that stops here so overall pretty convenient even for non-drivers.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Tranquil and peaceful place to get away from the hectic city life. Fortunately it was very cooling after a heavy downpour just hours before we arrived. The air was very fresh and not much crowd.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Unless you are an avid bird watcher, any visitation to this remote place should be with the guided walks. Date availability for such walks are quite limited.

The majority of the area is closed off to the public, and the most you'll get to experience is climbing to the top of the Raptor Tower. Not being a bird-watcher myself, there were few points of interest outside of the restricted zone. I was unlucky enough to not have seen any uncommon birds.

As accessibility to this place is low, Kranji Marshes remains void of visitors even on the weekends. You will have to walk for ~1km from the entrance into the marshes. Cycling, skating or PMDs of any sort are not permitted.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: A quiet and scenic park to take a stroll

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: The place is hard to go to even if you have transport for it. Very near to d'kranji resort. When you reach the entrance, it is actually a small place until you walk in and you will find a long stretch of road you need to walk through before getting to the observation tower. The place is actually quite alright, just getting is the problem.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Nothing much to see here. Good for exploration if you want to see some of SIngapore's more quiet parks/nature reserves, but really...there's nothing much (even if you are a bird enthusiast, only one observation tower could be quite sad)

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Good place for a nature hike  . Kranji marsh however is much smaller than Sungei Buloh Wetland and can be covered under 2 hrs .

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Kranji Marshes is located in a remote part of the Kranji area. It consists of a small manicured park at the start which lead to a small road that runs parallel to a canal. It takes about 20 minutes to walk to the end of the road and then you have to take the same road back to the start again.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Admittedly an extremely underwhelming experience compared to Sungei Buloh. To reach the tower, you have to walk for approximately 1km on a narrow road and the view at the top isn’t much. Fortunately for me though, I managed to spot a crocodile, only to realize it has frozen in time in stone.

Nonetheless, if you have time and want so peace and quiet in nature then do check it out as there was only 2 other groups when I visited on a Saturday early noon. There’s also a toilet at the entrance to relieve yourself if needed.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: Awesome park, with excellent bird species to boot. Guaranteed fun and nature experience.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text: It's a very short but serene walk. Not as many mosquito but I will still recommend getting protected if you are mostly a mosquito pin cushion.

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
Singapore's largest fresh water swamp. Most of the swamp area are not open to public. Guided tour to the non open area are available by NParks and Singapore Nature Society. The former conducts the tour in the afternoon and the latter in the morning.  The tours are conducted twice a month on advanced booking basis. There is a Kranji Express Bus service that goes right into the park. The charges is $3 for adults, $1 for children and senior citizen.

There is a Rapier Tower where you can climb up to have a view of the whole swamp.

name: Kranji Marshes
review_text:
It is located by the banks of the Kranji Reservoir.To reach it you have to drive along Neo Tiew Road, then turned left into Neo Tiew Lane 2, drive pass D'Kranji Farm Resort till you see the entrance of the Kranji Marshes.Parking is free  but have to leave before 7.00pm as the place will be closed.It is a good place to have a nice walk or hike to relax and lower the pressure from work and hassle of the city.Umbrellas, hats,raincoats,refreshments, insect repalents are some of the things advise to bring along.
Dated : 01/08/2017 ( Tuesday ).

The most exciting thing of the road was the wild boar sign. The spiral tower area and surroundings are very beautiful, but is also very small.
